<p><strong>IMPORTANT:</strong> This Assignment Addendum is ONLY presented when the jurisdiction ({{jurisdictionState}}{{#if jurisdictionCounty}}, {{jurisdictionCounty}} County{{/if}}) permits the assignment of surplus recovery claims. The inclusion of this addendum has been determined by the SurplusFlow jurisdiction rule engine based on applicable laws. REQUIRES LEGAL VERIFICATION — assignment provisions must be verified by licensed counsel before use in any jurisdiction.</p>

<hr style="margin: 20px 0;">

<p>This Assignment Addendum ("Addendum") is attached to and made a part of the Surplus Recovery Service Agreement ("Agreement") between <strong>{{companyName}}</strong> ("Company" or "Assignee") and <strong>{{claimantFullName}}</strong> ("Claimant" or "Assignor"), dated {{formatDate effectiveDate}}.</p>

<h2>1. ASSIGNMENT OF CLAIM</h2>

<p>1.1. The Claimant hereby assigns to the Company a limited interest in the surplus funds described in the Agreement, solely for the purpose of authorizing the Company to act on the Claimant's behalf in pursuing recovery of the funds.</p>

<p>1.2. This assignment is limited to the right to file, pursue, and administer the claim. It does <strong>NOT</strong> assign ownership of the underlying property or the full right to the surplus funds.</p>

<p>1.3. The assignment is effective only for the duration of the Agreement and automatically terminates upon termination of the Agreement or upon successful recovery and payment of the Success Fee.</p>

<h2>2. LIMITATIONS</h2>

<p>2.1. This assignment does not authorize the Company to receive funds directly. All recovered funds must be paid directly to the Claimant.</p>

<p>2.2. The Company shall not further assign, sell, or transfer this limited interest to any third party without the Claimant's prior written consent.</p>

<p>2.3. The Claimant retains all rights to the underlying property and surplus funds not expressly assigned herein.</p>

<h2>3. REVOCATION</h2>

<p>3.1. The Claimant may revoke this assignment at any time by providing written notice to the Company. Revocation of the assignment also constitutes termination of the Agreement, subject to the terms therein regarding fees for work already performed.</p>

{{#ifTrue coolingOffDays}}
<p>3.2. This assignment is subject to the same Cooling-Off Period described in the Agreement ({{coolingOffDays}} calendar days from signing). If the Claimant exercises their rescission right, this assignment is automatically void.</p>
{{/ifTrue}}

<h2>4. REPRESENTATIONS</h2>

<p>4.1. The Claimant represents that they are the rightful owner or heir to the surplus funds and have the legal authority to make this limited assignment.</p>

<p>4.2. The Claimant represents that they have not previously assigned these rights to any other party.</p>

